    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Works in which paint is applied on a textile support with only a thin glue preparation or no preparation; the painting surface remains flexible, and the works are often rolled and portable. These works were popular in Germany, the Netherlands, and Italy. For similar works on textiles having a thin gesso preparation, popular in Spain and its colonies, prefer "sargas (visual works)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093897/Metropolitan Museum of Art [online] (2001-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000062077/Roy, "The Technique of a Tüchlein, National Gallery Technical Bulletin (1988) </Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Werken waarin verf wordt aangebracht op een textieldrager die alleen dun met lijm is voorbewerkt of helemaal niet is voorbewerkt. Het oppervlak van de schildering blijft buigzaam en de werken kunnen worden opgerold en meegenomen. Deze werken waren populair in Duitsland, Nederland en Italië. Gebruik 'sarga's (beeldmateriaal)' voor soortgelijke werken op textiel met een dunne voorbewerking met gesso, populair in Spanje en zijn koloniën.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Trabalhos nos quais a tinta é aplicada sobre um suporte têxtil com somente uma fina preparação de aglutinação ou sem preparação; a superfície da pintura permanece flexível e os trabalhos são frequentemente enrolados e portáteis. Esses trabalhos são populares na Alemanha, na Holanda e na Itália. Para trabalhos similares em têxteis que contèm um fina preparação de gesso, popular na Espanha e em suas colônias, prefira "sargas (obras visuais)".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000110648/Portuguese Translation Intern Project (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
